The paper deals with data integration and quality issues in Linked Data, which are common topics in the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The approach proposed in the paper involves modeling correlations and dependencies between objects and sources, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SI). The use of Markov Random Fields (MRFs) is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and is also mentioned in the paper.
